        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 6:14AM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 613 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Northville, or 13 miles northeast of Gloversville, moving east at 65
mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northville, Fairchilds Corners, Big Hollow, Beartown, Tenantville,
Sweets Crossing, Lake Luzerne, Fourth Lake, Conklingville, Maple
Grove, Cranberry Creek, Carpenters Corners, Tomantown, Osbourne
Bridge, Hartman, Corinth, Lake Luzerne-Hadley, West Glens Falls,
Jackson Summit, and Lake Luzerne Campground.

This includes Interstate 87 near exit 18.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
